it also depends on the quality

76
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:53,730
of the information available.

77
00:03:53,730 --> 00:03:57,500
DHIS2 has many data quality
features that help ensure

78
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:01,350
that data is accurate before
it's used to make a decision.

79
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:04,110
These include the
ability to validate data,

80
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:05,970
identify duplicate entries,

81
00:04:05,970 --> 00:04:09,100
and flag abnormal values for review.

82
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:11,640
Managers can see an audit
trail of all entries

83
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:14,293
and changes and review summary reports.

84
00:04:15,770 --> 00:04:20,060
Once data is validated,
it's ready to be analyzed.

85
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:23,120
